## Workflow

| Step | Phase | Tools / Actions |
|------|-------|-----------------|
| ① | **Recon** | NetDiscover (host discovery), Nmap (port & service scan) |
| ② | **Attack** | Hydra (brute force), xfreerdp (RDP login attempts) |
| ③ | **Log Generation** | Windows Security Event 4625, Universal Forwarder → Splunk |
| ④ | **Detection** | SPL queries, Splunk dashboard (line / area / single value charts) |
| ⑤ | **Defense** | Windows Firewall rule — block attacker IP |
| ⑥ | **Documentation** | GitHub, slides, recorded walkthrough |

---

## Tech Stack

- **Attacker**: Kali Linux — NetDiscover, Nmap, Hydra, xfreerdp
- **Victim**: Windows Server — Splunk Universal Forwarder
- **SIEM**: Splunk Enterprise (index: `main`, listening on port `9997`)
- **Log source**: Windows Security Log (EventID 4625 — failed logon)

