## Defense — Firewall Rule

After identifying the attacker IP in Splunk, a Windows Firewall inbound rule is created to block all traffic from `<ATTACKER_IP>`:

```powershell
New-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName "Block Attacker" `
  -Direction Inbound `
  -RemoteAddress <ATTACKER_IP> `
  -Action Block
```

